title: eila_ilmatar_juutilainen
body:
Eila Ilmatar Juutilainen (エイラ・イルマタル・ユーティライネン, Eira Irumataru Yūtirainen?) is a witch of the [[501st Joint Fighter Wing]], originating from [[Suomus]] and affiliated with the Suomus Air Force. She is referred to as "Illu" by her friends, and is sometimes named Diamond Ace. Her familiar is the black [[fox]].

Eila's magic ability Foresight (未来予知, Mirai Yochi) grants her a limited ability to predict the future. Her hobby is fortune-telling with tarot cards, although the accuracy of her predictions is questionable at best. Similar to stereotypes of her familiar (the black fox), she has a reputation for mischief, being fond of pranks amongst her colleagues and is somewhat mischievous.

Eila is often partnered with 501st Night Witch [[Sanya V. Litvyak]], and perhaps as a result (perhaps it is simply chemistry) the two have become very close; Eila is often portrayed as fiercely protective of her younger squadmate and takes on a sometimes awkwardly nurturing role during down-time. Whether this interest is romantic or plain, big-sisterly fondness is up for interpretation. 

Eila is based on the #1-ranked Finnish flying ace (and #1-ranked non-German flying ace) "Eino Ilmari Juutilainen":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eino_Juutilainen. Like Eila, he bore the nickname "Illu" amongst his friends. Her magic ability, Foresight, is a reference to Eino having never been hit by enemy fire.

She has an older sister, [[Aurora E. Juutilainen|Aurora E. Juutilainen]].

title: aramaki_shinji
body:
[b]Aramaki Shinji[/b] (荒牧 伸志) (born October 2, 1960) is a Japanese anime director and mechanical designer, born in Fukuoka Prefecture. He was a member of Artmic.

He is noted for work on [[power_armor|powered exoskeletons]] and his [[mecha]] and CG design on several anime series.

Aramaki created mecha designs for many 80s and 90s anime series such as [[Kikou Souseiki Mospeada]] (the [[Mospeada (mecha)|]], the [[Legioss]]), [[Megazone 23]] (the [[Garland (megazone_23)|]]), [[Bubblegum Crisis]] and [[Gasaraki]]. More recently he designed mecha for [[Wolf's Rain]], [[Raideen (series)|]], [[Viper's Creed]] and [[Halo Legends]].

Many of his mecha designs are related or influenced by [[real life]] [[motorcycle]] designs, since he is an user and fan of that type of vehicles.

Aramaki has also directed several anime productions, including [i]Megazone 23[/i], [i]Gasaraki[/i], [[Appleseed]] and [i]Halo Legends[/i].

title: raglan_sleeves
body:
Raglan sleeves are sleeves attached to a garment via a diagonal seam from the armpit to the neckline (rather than a simple circular seam at the edge of the shoulder). They are often made in a different color than the torso of the garment and are constructed from one piece of material. Raglan sleeves are commonly used in sportswear, as they are designed to give greater freedom of movement for the arm and shoulder. 

T-shirts with this type of sleeve are sometimes called "baseball shirts" due to their popularity of use as undershirts for baseball uniforms. Raglan sleeves became very popular in fashion outside of sports in the start of the 1970's.

To add humiliation to lack of presence, he can only be seen when his balding head is exposed. His name derives from "影が薄い" - "kage ga usui" ("overshadowed"), and his surname also refers to his thinning hairline.

Fell in love with her homeroom teacher [[Itoshiki Nozomu]] and ultimately began stalking him and donning a [[kimono]], specifically a [[meiji schoolgirl uniform]].

title: sekiutsu_maria_tarou
body:
A character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]].

Maria is a dark-skinned illegal immigrant from somewhere in Southeast Asia. Maria's adopted Japanese names spell out as "籍売ったろう" - "seki-uttaro" ("I'll sell my name") - alluding to the fact that she bought it from a young man who's willing to sell everything related to him. She also hoards food and refuse from garbage cans. A running gag is that she has an aversion to wearing panties, socks and shoes, and as such, goes to school without them.

Jun is the resident poet of [[Itoshiki Nozomu]]'s class and one of the few known males in his class. He is named after the founder of the Junkudou-Shouten (ジュンク堂書店) bookstore chain. He is known to tell tearjerker stories with an implied mocking purpose to his main listener.

title: komori_kiri
body:
A major character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]]. 

Kiri's name is a pun on the word "籠もりきり" - "komorikiri" ("recluse") - a play on her [[hikikomori]] lifestyle. She is often seen covered by a blanket. Accidentally frightened out of her home by her homeroom teacher [[Itoshiki Nozomu]] and classmate [[Fuura Kafuka]] while the former was encouraging her to come to school, and has since been a permanent fixture in the school, as well as a caretaker to her teacher and his nephew [[itoshiki_majiru|Majiru]].

title: kitsu_chiri
body:
A major character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]].

Chiri is the (acting) Class Representative for Class 2-へ ("2-He" or "2-6"/"2-F"), whose name in hiragana, when compressed, can read "きっちり" - "kitchiri" ("exact") - referring to her obsession with equality and conformity. Her first name also lends itself to the words "埋める" - "umeru" ("bury") - and "千里眼" - "senrigan" ("clairvoyance") - alluding to her favorite weapon, a [[shovel|spade]], and her third eye, respectively.

title: kino_kuniya
body:
A character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]].

One of [[Itoshiki Nozomu]]' few known male students and [[Kudou Jun]]'s self-proclaimed rival in storytelling, but is otherwise better known for his awful fashion sense. His name comes from [i]Books Kinokuniya[/i], Japan's largest bookstore chain.

title: kaga_ai
body:
A character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]]. 

An extremely shy, insecure girl, whose name can mean "加害" - "kagai" ("perpetrate") - referring to her guilt complex, often apologizing for a lot of things, many of which are hardly her fault.

title: itoshiki_majiru
body:
A character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]].

Son of Enishi, (missing) eldest brother of the Itoshiki siblings. He currently hangs around with his uncle [[itoshiki_nozomu|Nozomu]] and looks up to the latter's student and de facto caretaker [[Komori Kiri]]. Like his uncles and aunt [[itoshiki_rin|Rin]], Majiru's name, when compressed, has another meaning: "絶交" - "zekkou" ("breach in relationships") - hinting to the fact that he has to live with his uncle.

title: itoshiki_kei
body:
A character in [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]].

Elder brother to [[itoshiki_mikoto|Mikoto]], [[itoshiki_nozomu|Nozomu]], and [[itoshiki_rin|Rin]]. His name, when compressed, forms the word "絶景" - "zekkei" ("superb scenery") - alluding to his profession as an eccentric surrealist painter with a stain on the wall for a "wife".

title: itoshiki_rin
body:
A character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]].

Youngest and only female of the Itoshiki siblings and a student of her immediate older brother [[itoshiki_nozomu|Nozomu]]. Her own name, compressed, becomes "絶倫" - "zetsurin" ("peerless") - referring to her skill at [i]ikebana[/i], but also, much to her ire, a slang related to sexual prowess. The anime adaptation also has her frequently facing her back to the audience, in reference to [[Nohara Shinnosuke]], or "Shin-chan", both of which were voiced by [[Yajima Akiko]].

title: itoshiki_mikoto
body:
A character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]].

Older brother to [[itoshiki_nozomu|Nozomu]] (both of whom look almost identical) and [[itoshiki_rin|Rin]], as well as a doctor who runs his own private clinic. However, like his siblings, his name also has an unfortunate connotation when compressed: his name can read as "絶命" - "zetsumei" ("death") - which explains the rarity of his patients. He could lose himself when called "zetsumei-sensei" ("Dr. Death").

title: hitou_nami
body:
A major character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]].

Nami's name is a pun on the word "人並み" - "hitonami" ("run-of-the-mill"). Compared to her homeroom teacher [[Itoshiki Nozomu|Nozomu]] and the rest of her classmates, Nami is otherwise completely normal, much to her distress - even her truancy and potentially self-destructive habits are considered normal for a neglected person like her. She is also known as an aficionado of [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] products.

title: fujiyoshi_harumi
body:
A character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]]

The resident doujin artist and [[yaoi]] fan of [[Itoshiki Nozomu]]'s class. Outside class, she often imagines various male-on-male pairings from various anime and manga, including her own teacher and some of her male classmates. Her tastes are often considered abnormal, in contrast to her orderly long-time classmate [[Kitsu Chiri]]. Her surname is a corruption of "腐女子" - "[[fujoshi]]" ("rotten girl"), a term for yaoi fangirls - and her given name derives from the former venue of the [[Comiket]] before it moved to [[Tokyo Big Sight]].

title: arai_chie
body:
A character from [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]].

Chie is the resident high school counselor. Her given name has an alternate reading - "Niichie", a reference to philosopher Friedrich Nietzsche. She is also known for her shapely body and sexual fetishism concerning masochistic males. Curiously enough, her most frequent visitor is teacher [[Itoshiki Nozomu]], who would come to her after another failed attempt at suicide, to air out his complaints against society.

title: itoshiki_nozomu
body:
Eponymous main character of [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]].

Nozomu is the homeroom teacher of high school class 2-へ ("2-He", or 2-6/2-F in modern notation). His own name, when compressed, spells out "絶望" - "zetsubou" ("despair") - befitting his extremely negative, suicidal personality. When not attempting suicide, he is normally heard complaining about current issues in Japan and abroad.

title: fuura_kafuka
body:
Principal female character of [[Sayonara Zetsubou Sensei]].

An extremely optimistic girl, and polar opposite of her homeroom teacher [[Itoshiki Nozomu]]. Her name is in reality a pen name derived from author Franz Kafka, which seems in stark contrast to her sunny nature, but may also hint to what some of her classmates perceive to be her hidden dark side.

title: rolento
body:
[b]Rolento F. Schugerg[/b] (ロレント・F・シュゲルグ), more commonly referred by his first name, is a video game character from both the [[Final Fight]] and [[Street Fighter]] series. Like [[Sodom]] before him, he first appeared as a boss character in the first Final Fight, but later evolved into a playable fighter in [[street_fighter_zero_(series)|Street Fighter Alpha 2]]. 

Rolento wears a [[military uniform]] with weapon belts (where he keeps his [[grenade]]s) going over his shoulders and a red beret on his head. He has a red scarf under his worn yellow outfit and fights with a green staff. This is a change from how he originally appeared in Final Fight, in which he wore an olive green uniform, and wielded a brown staff.

title: fei_long
body:
[b]Fei Long[/b] is a character in the [[Street Fighter]] series. 

Fei Long is a tribute to the Kung Fu movie legend [[Bruce Lee]]. Not only do the two look alike and come from the same city, Fei Long also lets out similar battle cries to Lee, and is just as furious and fast. Also, Fei Long is Mandarin for "flying dragon", as well as a type of kick. Bruce Lee's Chinese screen name was 李 小龍 (Li Xiao-Long) or "little dragon." He was one of the early Bruce Lee look-alike characters in fighting games.

A youthful and talented man from Hong Kong, Fei Long developed his own form of Kung Fu and fought on the streets to sharpen his skills until he caught the eye of a movie director, who got him into the movie business.

title: crimrose
body:
"[i]A female robot from an outer dimension. 50% of her body consist of Zias geo-cells, allowing her to move with grace and precision.[/i]"

A [[mecha musume]] from the game [[Cosmic Break]], Crimrose is shown to be a cheerful and carefree girl. As a robot, she is characterized by her long hair, peculiar feet, and her armor (more specifically her upper armor that barely cover any part of her chest).

She is the basic air unit players can get at the start of the game, and also has a [[chibi]] form. There are several variations of her hair color and parts in-game.

Crimrose is one of the few characters in [[Cosmic Break]] that currently have an alternate/'promotion' form, along with [[Lily Rain]], [[Winberrl]] and [[LazFlamme]]. Her alternate form is known as [[Seraph Crimrose]], characterized by a pair of additional wings protruding from her back.

She is pretty much considered the [[Cosmic Break]] mascot and one of the main characters of the Cosmic Break story. She is also featured as an NPC in the game.

While her story is still unclear, it is said in the mangas that she met [[Ivis]] in a research facility when they were younger, and died during experiments to find a host for a powerful weapon, along with several other children. Her death made Ivis go berserk, sucessfully activating the weapon and killing everyone in the facility. Crimrose was later revived at the Cosmic Ark without any memories of her time alive and met Ivis again, although the latter had developed an obssession for Crimrose because of the traumas she experienced in the research facility and, after learning that Crimrose didn't remember her and seeing her acting friendly towards other people, went berserk once again. Her rampage was stopped by Seraph Crimrose, fortunately before she killed anyone, and she escaped. It is stated in Ivis' in-game description that Crimrose bought her back to her senses, although this is never shown. 

Crimrose is later seen along with Ivis in Ground Area, talking to player about their ACs, and as a normal student in Angel Academy.

In the game [[Cosmic Break 2]], another Crimrose from the alternate timeline is one of the starter characters.

title: shiratori_rena
body:
A [[Virtual YouTuber]] and "V[[Voice actor]]" of [[Voice-Ore]], her emoji is 🏰. She debuted on February 24, 2021 as Voice-Ore production's first generation virtual voice actor, her Live2D was designed by [[nabi_(uz02)|Nabi]] and her rigging by Takeyanagi.

A 17 year old girl from an influential family, ever since she was young she has lived a carefully sheltered life raised "surrounded by butterflies and flowers". Because of the upbringing by her household she has rarely a chance to meet or interact with others that she could open her heart to, thus has a hard time showing her true feelings but deep down is a very expressive and [[tsundere]] young girl. Despite living under strict parents that banned all things anime and game related she still developed a love for them and secretly works toward her dream of becoming a voice actor. 

Her appearance is that of a [[blunt_bangs|blunt bang]] [[silver_hair|silvered]] prim and proper "Ojou-sama":https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Ojou with [[long_hair|long flowing hair]], giving off a very cool and elegant vibe but those that get close to her will see that she can be quite silly at times, especially during her "Rena teatime" when she interact and holds conversation with her chat regarding the weather, her day or how she is still sleepy right after having just gotten out of bed to stream. She wears a [[layered_dress|multi-layered]] [[long_sleeves|long sleeve]] [[white_dress|frilly white dress]] adorned in [[black_ribbon|ribbons]] and a [[brooch]] with a [[black_bow|black bow]]. Her eyes are [[blue_eyes|light blue-ish purple]] and she sports a slightly stoic yet sleepy look with jeweled [[earrings]] hidden behind on her ears.  

Rena understands English well enough to read and speak it, as well as understands German that she notes she's been studying. She enjoys fantasy and tea, as well as chocolate and other confectionery. As a "Vseiyuu", whenever she plays a game she would also tend to read out in-game texts in different ranges of voices based on what she think the character sounds like. She is friends with her fellow Voice-Ore members, [[Himukai_Kogane|Himukai Kogane]] and [[Aoi_Mizuki|Aoi Mizuki]], who often drop by in her chat and refer to them as Koga-chan and Mizuki-chan.

Her other emoji is also 🕊, a white bird/Dove based on her name "Shiratori ([b]白鳥[/b])" which reads as such respectively (white bird), and her personal greeting to her fans is [i]Guten Rena[/i] based on the German phrase of "Good morning/day ([i]Guten Tag/Morgen[/i]) and [i]Tschüss[/i] ("Good bye/Bye Bye" in German).  The official name for her fans is [b]Renavants[/b].

title: ever_given_(evergreen)
body:
The [i]Ever Given[/i] is a Golden-class container ship built by the Japanese Imabari Shipbuilding company and operated by the Taiwanese [[Evergreen Marine Corporation]].  She initially had a theoretical carrying capacity of 20,338 Twenty-foot Equivalent Units (TEU), the rough volume of 20,388 standard 20-foot long shipping containers.  After receiving a retrofit to add scrubbers to reduce emissions her theoretical carrying capacity was reduced to 20,124 TEU.

In February 2019, while on route from Hamburg, Germany to Rotterdam, Netherlands the [i]Ever Given[/i] collided and severely damaged the docked Hamburg ferry [i]Finkenwerder[/i].  This may have happened due to high winds at the time.

In March 2021, while traveling through the Suez Canal the [i]Ever Given[/i] was caught up in a sand storm and ran aground blocking the canal. It was finally freed from the canal after six days.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia - Ever Given":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ever_Given]

title: hijiri_myouren
body:
聖 命蓮

A "Heian era":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heian_period historical figure, approximately of the 11th or 12th century, Myouren was a Buddhist monk born in Shinano Province, or Nagano Prefecture, as it's known today. 

He trained at the Chougosonshi Temple (朝護孫子寺) on Mount Shigi (信貴山) near Nara, which he established. His most significant role is in the "[i]Shigisan-engi[/i]":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shigisan-engi emaki. 

The [i]Shigisan-engi[/i] is also the basis for [[Touhou|Touhou's]] [i][[Undefined Fantastic Object]][/i]. In it, it is told that he had an older sister, who was worried about him. So she searched for Myouren and after being reunited with him, the two lived together again. This woman is the basis for [[Hijiri Byakuren]], whose brother's later death drove her to despair and made her fear her own mortality.

His role in Touhou is minor, only serving as backstory for Byakuren. However, ZUN has said he once considered Myouren for a main role in UFO, albeit as an old man. No official character design exists for him, leaving his appearance up to speculation. Fanart typically depicts him with [[gradient hair]] like his sister's, despite the fact that a Buddhist monk would normally have [[bald|shaved off all his hair]].

h4. External links

* "Hijiri Myouren on Touhou Wiki":http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Myouren_Hijiri

title: mark_iv_tank
body:
The Mark IV Tank was the fourth iteration of the British heavy tank series during [[World War I]]. It featured major improvements over it's predecessors, particularly in terms of armor, fuel tank arrangement and ease of transportation. It retained the rhomboidal shape and guns mounted in sponsons on either side of the vehicle, but dropped the external steering wheels.

The Mark IV Tank was the most produced British tank of the First World War. It first saw action in June 1917 during the "Battle of Messines":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Messines_(1917), and participated in the first tank versus tank combat against German [[a7v_(tank)|A7Vs]] at the "Second Battle of Villers-Bretonneux":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Battle_of_Villers-Bretonneux.

h4. See also

title: baiken
body:
Character from [[Guilty Gear]] fighting game series.

A female [[samurai]] born in Japan amidst the "Crusades" during which millions of native Japanese people were killed by the Gears, leading to them being declared as an endangered species. During one of these attacks Baiken's parents were killed, she also lost her right arm (which she has since replaced with a [[claw_(weapon)|claw]]) and left eye to the Gears responsible for the death of her parents. From that day forward Baiken swore revenge on the creator of the Gears, known only as "That Man". 

h5. Visual characteristics
Baiken has a [[big_hair|voluminous]] [[pink hair]] worn in a [[ponytail]], a [[scar]] over her missing [[one-eyed|left eye]] and a [[facial tattoo]]. She wears a loose [[white kimono|white]] and [[black kimono|black]] [[multicolored kimono|kimono]] with the sleeves tucked in the sides of a [[kataginu]], showing off her [[large_breasts|large breasts]]. She also wears [[sash]], [[greaves]], [[sandals]], a [[eyepatch]] and a clawed grappling hook for her [[amputee|right arm]]. She has [[red eyes]] and is tipically depicted wielding a [[katana]]. In [[Guilty Gear Xrd]], her kimono is almost unchanged, though she now has a [[black jacket]] that she [[jacket on shoulders|wears on her shoulders]] like a cape.

title: u-2_dragon_lady
body:
An ultra high-altitude reconnaissance jet airplane, operated by the CIA during the Cold War to spy over the Soviet Union in all-weather, diurnal and nocturnal missions.
It was considered safe from attacks due to its service ceiling. There wasn't any kind of fighter jet or missile able to reach it. In 1960 one of them was shot down over Soviet Airspace.

It can be recognised by its high aspect ratio and huge wingspan (31 m) wich required supports while at ground and during take off. The wings are also classified as straight and tapered.

title: momotarou_densetsu
body:
Momotarou Densetsu is a series of games by [[Hudson]] directed by Sakuma Akira with art design by Doi Takayuki that started out as an RPG series in 1987. It was popular enough to spawn several spin-offs and an anime that itself received a further anime spin-off.

It's especially notable for the highly successful spin-off [[Momotarou Dentetsu]], a railway-based digital board game series that has outlived the success of the main series.

The games feature characters inspired by Japanese folk tales and various mythological sources. Each game also almost always have a voyeuristic [[onsen]] or [[bath]] scene "hidden in each game":https://namegepo.nomaki.jp/game_momohuro.html (NSFW) somewhere.

note: not to be confused with [[Momotarou]], the Japanese legend from which Momotarou Densetsu gets its inspiration.

title: a7v_(tank)
body:
The A7V was the only German tank to see combat in [[World War I]]. It is notable for its boxy shape, with every side featuring a weapons emplacement, being armed with one canon and six machine guns. It had a very high crew requirement at 18, and while it had good road speed it's cross-country capability was poor. Only 20 vehicles were produced, and the tank had little overall impact on the war.

The A7V first saw action on 21 March 1918 at the St. Quentin Canal, and also participated in the first tank versus tank combat against British [[mark_iv_tank|Mark IVs]] at the "Second Battle of Villers-Bretonneux":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Battle_of_Villers-Bretonneux.

title: levitate_(pokemon)

An ability in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]][/i] media which causes the user to float in the air.

Under normal conditions, a Pokémon with Levitate is unaffected by Ground-type moves, various ground-based moves such as Arena Trap, Spikes, etc. and also the various kinds of terrain. They share these immunities with Flying-type Pokémon.

In many cases, Pokémon that are seen floating in the air are the ones who may have Levitate as their ability: [[Gastly]], [[Koffing]], [[Lunatone]], [[Bronzong]], etc. However, in some cases the Pokémon may or may not have this ability.

There are also some Pokémon that are often seen levitating but can't have this ability in the first place (unless aided by other moves or abilities), such as [[Magnemite]] and [[Metang]].

title: tokonoma
body:
A tokonoma, or simply toko, is a built-in recessed space in a Japanese style reception room, in which items for artistic appreciation are displayed. In English, a tokonoma could be called an alcove. The word 'toko' literally means "floor" or "bed"; 'ma' means "space" or "room".

The items usually displayed in a tokonoma are calligraphic or pictorial scrolls and an arrangement of flowers. The pillar on one side of the tokonoma is usually made of wood, specially prepared for the purpose.
